<!-- Node: "A Game In Under 100K!" -->
<div class="body_box_header">A Game In Under 100K!</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/204" title="View user profile.">Miniwood</a> on Sunday, April 18, 2004 - 20:38</small><br /><br />
<center><img src="http://www.gamedesign.net/miniwood/images/kksnapshot1.jpg"></center>
<BR>
Believe it or not you are looking at a screenshot from a game that takes up less than 100k of you hard disk. That's about the size of a single texture for Unreal Tournament 2004.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>.Kkrieger</B> is a fairly basic FPS game and is only at the beta stage but you really have to wonder at how so much content can be produced by so little code.
<BR>
<BR>
Visit <A HREF="http://theprodukkt.com/">The Produkkt</A> for more screenshots and a near instantaneous download.
<BR>
<BR>
<font size="1">Thanks Ratz2010 at <A HREF="http://www.bdmcnet.com/forum/">The Big Guy's Forums</A></font>
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Free Game! - RuneSword 2 Goes Open Source." -->
<div class="body_box_header">Free Game! - RuneSword 2 Goes Open Source.</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/204" title="View user profile.">Miniwood</a> on Sunday, April 18, 2004 - 19:44</small><br /><br />
<A HREF="http://www.crosscutgames.com/index.html">Crosscut Games</A> has announced that their CRPG RuneSword 2 is now available free and that the code is open source and available on <A HREF="http://sourceforge.net/projects/runesword/">Source Forge</A>. 
<BR><BR>
They hope that the game will be further developed by the open source coding community:

<BLOCKQUOTE>Now, say you want to learn more about how a CRPG is made. Say you know Visual Basic. Or say you just want to help make RS2 even better. Now's your chance to get involved in the open source community! (Crosscut Games Website)</BLOCKQUOTE>
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/233" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a> &middot; 95 reads
